Descriptor.0: CAM>Charge and Mass Magnetospheric Ion Composition

TEXT.0: This data set contains 96-second averaged counting rates for H+, He++, (O+, O++ together), (O>2+), all from the MICS part of the instrument, with a +/- 1 degree field of view perpendicular to the spin axis, segmented into bins of size 1/32 of a spin.

TEXT.1: T.A. Fritz et.al, CAMMICE:The POLAR CAMMICE instruments

TEXT.2: It also contains 96-second averaged counting rates from two proton channels (0.5-1.7 MeV and 1.7-5.8 MeV), two He channels (1.4-4.3 MeV and 4.3-9.6 MeV), and six CNO channels (5-10, 6-11, 7-13, 17-92, 18-92, 21-92 MeV), from the HIT part of the instrument, with a +/- 6 degree field of view perpendicular to the spin axis, segmented into bins

TEXT.4: A. Fritz et.al, CAMMICE:The POLAR CAMMICE instruments

MODS.0: This is the 1st version, generated on 17 November 1995.

Logical_source_description.0: ~2.3-minute Key Parameters, CAMMICE/Polar Charge And Mass Magnetospheric Ion Composition Experiment
